  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Save sexual minorities from hate crimes in Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project focus on sensitizing 40 religious leaders drawn from the two major religions to be trained in Abuja metropolis of Nigeria towards stopping advocacy towards passing discriminatory laws that endanger the rights of sexual minorities in Nigeria. The bill currently supported by some religious leaders if passed into law will fuel hate crimes and violence regardless of constitutionally guaranteed fundamental rights as enshrined in the 1999 Constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria.</narrative>
  </description>
